//@version=6
indicator("Commander Bull Screener v3.2", overlay=true)
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v3.3 (2026-05-21) — POS-ACCUM rollback
// ==========================================
// 1. POS-ACCUM catalyst RE-ENABLED (live). The v3.2 disable below is SUPERSEDED.
//    Reason: the -10.04% backtest used a 30-day forward window, which is the
//    wrong horizon for a Stage 1->2 accumulation setup designed for 6-8 month
//    positional holds. Live code assigns catalyst_id := 1 on is_pos_accum (no
//    `false and` guard). Still gated by dailyRsi <= pos_accum_rsi_max (50).
//    Mirrors bull_screener.py v1.10 + Unified Ecosystem v3.6. See
//    validation_window_mismatch_warning.md.
//
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v3.2 (2026-05-20) — Backtest-validated patches
// ==========================================
// 1. [SUPERSEDED by v3.3 — POS-ACCUM is now RE-ENABLED, see above]
//    POS-ACCUM catalyst DISABLED. Backtest (Nifty 500 × 12 anchors, May 2025-
//    Apr 2026): n=5 picks, 0 wins, -10.04% mean alpha. (Historical record only;
//    the live code does NOT contain a `false and is_pos_accum` guard.)
// 2. JdK 2-pass RRG formula (length=12 + 5-bar smooth). Matches Strike.Money
//    93.8% (vs 66.7% for old dual-SMA Mansfield). Parity with Dashboard v67.4
//    + Ecosystem v3.0 + Python bull_screener.py v1.7.
// 3. RRG score: +2 if LEADING else 0 (was +5/-10/-5 matrix). Recalibrated on
//    n=5,020 backtest after JdK switch — only LEADING quadrant kept material
//    alpha (+1.24%); others clustered near zero. Matches bull_screener.py v1.7
//    + Dashboard v67.4.3.
//
// ==========================================

// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v3.1 — COMPOSITE-MERGE PASS
// ==========================================
// FOLLOW-UP to v3.0: v3.0 removed duplicate rows but didn't merge the remaining
// rows. v3.1 applies Dashboard-style composite merging:
//
// MERGED:
//   ── SETUP VERDICT section (was 4 rows: Catalyst · Signal · Alpha · Confluence)
//      → 1 compound VERDICT row:
//          "SWG-PB · WAIT · A+ (90/100) · Conf 5/6 · 4 gate(s) blocking"
//   ── POS-BO GATES (was 9 individual rows: G1 … G9)
//      → 5 paired rows (G1+G2, G3+G4, G5+G6, G7+G8, G9 solo).
//        Drilldown clarity preserved — each gate still has its own coloured
//        ✓/✗ cell. G7 carries the macro-week count inline (e.g. "G7 Fresh (40w)").
//   ── TRADE LEVELS (was 5 rows: Price · SL · T1 · T2 · Signal Today)
//      → 1 compound LEVELS row:
//          "P 1113.00 · SL 1057.35 (5.0%) · T1 1224.30 (2R) · T2 1279.95 (3R) · Sig —"
//
// LAYOUT (v3.1, ~13 rows total):
//   Title row (full width)
//   🎯 VERDICT header                            (1)
//   VERDICT compound                             (1)
//   ⚙️ POS-BO GATES X/9 header w/ status pill   (1)
//   G1+G2 paired                                 (1)
//   G3+G4 paired                                 (1)
//   G5+G6 paired                                 (1)
//   G7+G8 paired                                 (1)
//   G9 solo                                      (1)
//   → See Dashboard footer                       (1)
//   📋 TRADE LEVELS header                       (1)
//   LEVELS compound                              (1)
//   🛠 HOW TO TRADE header w/ status pill       (1)
//   ENTRY / SIZE                                 (1)
//   CONFIRM / MANAGE                             (1)
//   RISK / KEY LVL                               (1)
//
// NEW HELPERS: drawRowC (full-width composite row), drawGatePair (two-gate row).
// LOGIC UNCHANGED — display-layer-only compression.
// ==========================================

// ============================================================================
//  CROSS-TOOL ARCHITECTURE — v3.0 (Decision-Mode Compression Pass)
// ============================================================================
//  The Dashboard (Weinstein & Swing Pro Dashboard v67.3.0+) is now the canonical
//  source for: RS engine · Stage anchors · Strict trend · Price Action Structure
//  · Portfolio · Persona / Style · Volume Trend · EMA Proximity.
//
//  This Screener stays canonical for: Catalyst detection · 9-gate POS-BO stack
//  · Trade Levels (pivot-based SL / T1 / T2) · Confluence score · Bull-specific
//  Alpha Grade · "How to trade" guidance.
//
//  Result: rows that duplicated the Dashboard's display were REMOVED. The
//  underlying computations are still performed (the catalyst engine consumes
//  them), but they no longer occupy table real estate here.
// ============================================================================

// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v3.0 — DECISION-MODE COMPRESSION + RS ENGINE MIRROR
// ==========================================
// ARCHITECTURAL: Dashboard is now the canonical source for the RS / Mansfield
//   engine (see Dashboard guide §16). The Screener mirrors Dashboard's
//   f_calc_rs_logic exactly — dual-SMA (26w for slope-Mansfield, 52w for
//   level-Mansfield), 8w slope window, 4-bar momentum, 130-bar warm-up gate.
//
// CHANGE: f_calc_rs_logic — dual-SMA signature (rsl, rslLevel, slopeLen).
//   Returns [slope, mrsLevel, pastSlope, rs_mom] (was 3-tuple).
//   New input `rsLevelLen` (default 52). `rsSlopeLen` default 5 → 8 to match
//   Dashboard. Existing tooltips reference Dashboard.
//
// CHANGE: f_rsStateStr — true RRG quadrant semantics. Old logic was slope-
//   driven (e.g. "Leading" when slope > thresh regardless of level), which
//   diverged from RRG convention and from Dashboard. New logic:
//     LEADING   = level > 0 AND momentum > 0
//     WEAKENING = level > 0 AND momentum <= 0
//     LAGGING   = level <= 0 AND momentum <= 0
//     IMPROVING = level <= 0 AND momentum > 0
//   Slope direction appended as "(Rising|Falling|Flat)" suffix for context.
//
// REMOVED (Dashboard owns these — read them there):
//   STAGE row              · RS N500 row    · RS SECTOR row
//   RRG QUAD row           · VOL SHELF row  · OBV TREND row
//   VCP TIGHT row          · MINERVINI TT row
//   REL VOLUME row         · DIST EMA20 row
//   (the entire "RS & QUALITY" right-column section)
//   Net: 10 rows removed; cell-clutter down ~30 %.
//
// REORGANIZED — table now follows the catalyst-decision workflow:
//   LEFT  COLUMN (DIAGNOSIS):
//     ── SETUP VERDICT ── (Catalyst → Signal → Alpha/Grade → Confluence)
//     ── POS-BO GATES X/9 ── (G1 … G9, the workflow drill-down)
//     → See Dashboard for: RS · Stage · Trend · Vol · Persona (footer)
//   RIGHT COLUMN (TRADE PLAN):
//     ── TRADE LEVELS ── (Price → SL → T1 → T2 → Signal Today)
//     ── HOW TO TRADE / WATCH MODE ── (Entry · Confirm · Risk · Size · Manage · Key Level)
//
// LOGIC UNCHANGED: every catalyst, gate, score and trade-level formula
//   continues to compute exactly as before. Internal RS calculations now
//   match the Dashboard's, so G3 (Sector RS) gate behaviour shifts slightly:
//   stocks where the prior slope-driven engine said "Leading" but level<0 will
//   now correctly classify as "Improving" (the correct RRG quadrant).
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v2.9 (Score-formula alignment with bull_screener.calculate_score, 2026-05-10)
//   • Added pyScore: composite quality score that mirrors Python's
//     bull_screener.calculate_score() formula component-for-component:
//       Catalyst tier (POS-BO/SWG-BO/SWG-GAP=30, SWG-REV=20, SWG-PB=10, POS-ACCUM=15)
//       Stage 2 (10), Mansfield RS (10+10), Mansfield 4w momentum (5),
//       RRG quadrant (-10/-5/+5), Volume tier (5/10/15),
//       Sector strength (-5/+5), Trend template (10), Dist 52W high (3/5/7/10).
//     Clamped to [0, 100].
//   • Added input use_python_aligned_score (default TRUE):
//     when ON, the displayed `score` variable is overwritten with pyScore so
//     dashboards show the Python-aligned value. When OFF, native Pine score
//     (Stage25 + RS15 + slope15 + alpha_q3+_h1 + liq_sweep) is preserved.
//   • Added defensive-mode toggle days_since_pivot_penalty_on (default FALSE):
//     mirrors v2_fixes.V2_FLAGS["days_since_pivot_penalty"]. When ON,
//     pyScore -= 10 if bars since last isBreakout > days_since_pivot_max.
//     Surface for ad-hoc enabling in market drawdowns; not a default.
//   • days_since_pivot tracked via var int last_breakout_bar updated on isBreakout.
//   • Source: BACKTEST_RESULTS_v2.docx §7 + bull_screener.calculate_score lines 454-561.
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v2.8 (Signal-drift sync — v2 FINAL config lock, 2026-05-10)
//   • Added "POS-ACCUM RSI gate" input: pos_accum_rsi_max (default 50).
//   • is_pos_accum now also requires dailyRsi <= pos_accum_rsi_max.
//   • Mirrors Python v2_fixes.adjust_catalyst_score behavior: POS-ACCUM
//     should not fire when daily RSI > 50 (late-stage chase trap).
//   • Note: Python nullifies the +15 score contribution but keeps the
//     POS-ACCUM label. Pine's alphaScore has no equivalent +15 boost,
//     so we gate the catalyst label itself — same downstream effect on
//     pick selection, slightly stricter on labelling.
//   • Source: BACKTEST_RESULTS_v2.docx §7.1; v2 ablation Run 20260508_204424
//     (raw +0.14pp α held hit) and 20260508_224037 (filtered +0.26pp α held hit).
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v2.7 (Signal-drift sync — v1 FINAL config lock, 2026-05-08)
//   • Added "Hunter Scan — v1 FINAL" input group with two explicit inputs:
//       hunter_weekly_rsi_min (default 60, was hardcoded 55-equivalent)
//       hunter_daily_adx_min  (default 25, was structural bool only)
//   • f_calc_adx_bool() renamed f_calc_adx(); now returns [bool, float ADX].
//   • hunter_adx_ok = d_adx_val >= hunter_daily_adx_min (numeric gate).
//   • POS-BO catalyst condition now requires:
//       wRsiVal >= hunter_weekly_rsi_min AND hunter_adx_ok
//     in addition to all existing weinstein_setup + isBreakout gates.
//   • Zero signal drift vs chartink_replay.SCAN_PARAMS (v1_FINAL_20260508).
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v2.5 (Hygiene sync with Strategy v4.52)
//   • Added explicit lookahead=barmerge.lookahead_off to all 5
//     request.security() calls (was implicit-default; now explicit per v4.52
//     hygiene policy).
//   • Tightened EMA-pullback zone from ±2.0% to ±1.5% to exactly match Pine
//     Strategy v4.52 input default (was approximated previously).
//   • Expanded weinstein_setup from 5 gates to 9 by porting vol_acc_ok,
//     stage2_fresh_ok, ma_sqz_ok, bb_sqz_ok from Pine Strategy v4.52
//     line 937. POS-BO and POS-ACCUM now require the same institutional
//     accumulation + freshness + squeeze conditions as the canonical
//     strategy.
// ==========================================
//
// CHANGELOG v2.4 (Sync with Strategy v4.52 & Dashboard ULTIMATE v3.7)
//   • Added alpha_ok (Score >= 60) gate to POS-BO, SWG-PB, SWG-BO, and POS-ACCUM.
//   • Widened SWG-BO Pivot lookback from 10 to 15.
//   • Added Stage 1/2 and wRSI > 40 guards to SWG-REV.
//   • Added intraday position > 0.60 filter and low-bar SL for SWG-GAP.
//   • Added POS-BO trend_template_ok gate (within 25% of ATH, >30% from 52W low).
//   • Deduped VCP logic and added volume VWMA conditions.
//   • Updated Mansfield to True ×100 Scale and RRG Quadrant.
//   • Fixed Stage State Initialization and time-based Stage Weeks tracking.
// ==========================================

// ==========================================
// 1. STRATEGY INPUTS (For Finetuning)
// ==========================================
groupStrat  = "Strategy Inputs"
maLengthW   = input.int(30, title="Weinstein SMA Length (Weekly)", group=groupStrat)
wmaSlopeLen = input.int(6, title="30 WMA Slope Lookback (Weeks)", group=groupStrat)
slopeThresh = input.float(0.0012, title="30WMA Slope Threshold (Flat)", group=groupStrat)

bench50     = input.symbol("NSE:NIFTY",  title="Benchmark (Nifty 50)",          group=groupStrat)   // ENHANCEMENT v2.1: Nifty 50 RS
bench500    = input.symbol("NSE:CNX500", title="Benchmark (Nifty 500/Breadth)", group=groupStrat)

// v3.0: RS engine now mirrors the canonical Dashboard implementation
// (dual-SMA: 26w for slope-Mansfield, 52w for level-Mansfield, 8w slope window).
// See Dashboard guide §16 for why Dashboard is the canonical source.
rsLength    = input.int(26, title="Mansfield RS Slope SMA (Weeks)", group=groupStrat, tooltip="v3.0: now the SMA used for the SLOPE Mansfield calculation. Must match Dashboard's rsLength.")
rsLevelLen  = input.int(52, title="Mansfield RS Level SMA (Weeks)", group=groupStrat, tooltip="v3.0 NEW: SMA for the LEVEL Mansfield (canonical Weinstein definition). Must match Dashboard's rsLevelLen.")
rsSlopeLen  = input.int(8,  title="RS Slope Lookback (Weeks)",      group=groupStrat, tooltip="v3.0: bumped from 5 → 8 to match Dashboard's slope window. The wider window produces smoother slope readings — for short-term momentum, see Dashboard's RS Momentum.")

groupMA     = "Daily MA Settings"
dma50_len   = input.int(50, title="50 DMA Length", group=groupMA)
dma150_len  = input.int(150, title="150 DMA Length", group=groupMA)
dma200_len  = input.int(200, title="200 DMA Length", group=groupMA)
dmaSlopeLen = input.int(21, title="50DMA Slope Lookback (Days)", group=groupMA)
flatThresh  = input.float(0.0005, title="Slope Flat Threshold (Daily)", group=groupMA)

groupTech   = "Technical Settings"
atrLen      = input.int(14, title="ATR Length", group=groupTech)

grp_edge = "Mathematical Edges (Backtested)"
use_macro_edge = input.bool(true, title="[ENABLE] Macro Edge: Institutional Vol Bias", group=grp_edge)

grp_hunter = "Hunter Scan — v1 FINAL (Locked 2026-05-08)"
hunter_weekly_rsi_min = input.int(60, title="Hunter Weekly RSI Min", group=grp_hunter, minval=40, maxval=80, tooltip="v1 FINAL: 60 (was 55). Must match chartink_replay.SCAN_PARAMS[hunter][weekly_rsi_min].")
hunter_daily_adx_min  = input.int(25, title="Hunter Daily ADX Min",  group=grp_hunter, minval=10, maxval=50, tooltip="v1 FINAL: 25 (was 20). Must match chartink_replay.SCAN_PARAMS[hunter][daily_adx_min].")

grp_v2 = "v2 FINAL — Catalyst Filters (Locked 2026-05-10)"
pos_accum_rsi_max = input.int(50, title="POS-ACCUM Daily RSI Max", group=grp_v2, minval=30, maxval=70, tooltip="v2 LOCKED: POS-ACCUM catalyst suppressed when dailyRsi > this value. Mirrors v2_fixes.V2_PARAMS[pos_accum_rsi_threshold]. Reason: late-stage POS-ACCUM at high RSI is a chase trap (HCLTECH-style failure).")
vcp_mult_bo = input.float(1.875, title="VCP ATR Mult (Breakout)", group=grp_v2, minval=0.5, maxval=5.0, tooltip="VCP ATR multiplier for breakout setups.")
vcp_mult_swg = input.float(1.50, title="VCP ATR Mult (Swing)", group=grp_v2, minval=0.5, maxval=5.0, tooltip="VCP ATR multiplier for swing setups.")

grp_v29 = "v2.9 — Python-Aligned Score & Defensive Toggle"
use_python_aligned_score = input.bool(true,  title="Use Python-Aligned pyScore (recommended)", group=grp_v29, tooltip="When ON, the displayed Score mirrors Python's bull_screener.calculate_score() — same components, same weights. When OFF, native Pine score (Stage+RS+slope+alpha_vs_bench+liq_sweep) is preserved.")
days_since_pivot_penalty_on = input.bool(false, title="Defensive Mode: Days_Since_Pivot Penalty", group=grp_v29, tooltip="Mirrors v2_fixes.V2_FLAGS[days_since_pivot_penalty]. When ON, pyScore -= 10 if bars since last isBreakout exceed Days_Since_Pivot_Max. Backtest evidence: lifts hit-rate but truncates upside on filtered universe. Use only in market drawdowns where hit-rate matters more than alpha.")
days_since_pivot_max         = input.int(30, title="Days_Since_Pivot Max (bars)", group=grp_v29, minval=10, maxval=120, tooltip="Mirrors v2_fixes.V2_PARAMS[days_since_pivot_max].")
days_since_pivot_pen_pts     = input.int(10, title="Days_Since_Pivot Penalty Points", group=grp_v29, minval=1, maxval=30, tooltip="Mirrors v2_fixes.V2_PARAMS[days_since_pivot_penalty].")

// Webhook Alerts Group
grp_alert = "Webhook Alerts"
use_webhook_json = input.bool(false, title="Send JSON Webhook Alerts (Ngrok + Webhook)", group=grp_alert, tooltip="If enabled, alerts will be formatted as JSON for the webhook server.")
portfolio_capital = input.float(100000.0, title="Total Capital (INR)", step=10000.0, group=grp_alert)
risk_per_trade_pct = input.float(0.75, title="Risk per Trade (%)", minval=0.1, step=0.05, group=grp_alert)
max_alloc = input.float(25000.0, title="Max Allocation per Trade", step=5000.0, group=grp_alert)

grp_disp = "Display"
tbl_pos_input = input.string("Top Right", title="Table Position",
     options=["Top Right", "Top Left", "Top Center",
              "Middle Right", "Middle Center", "Middle Left",
              "Bottom Right", "Bottom Left", "Bottom Center"],
     group=grp_disp)

// ==========================================
// 2. HELPER FUNCTIONS & SECTOR MAPPER
// ==========================================
f_calc_slope_val(series float src, int len) =>
    ta.linreg(src, len, 0) - ta.linreg(src, len, 1)

f_get_sector_ticker() =>
    string s = str.lower(str.tostring(syminfo.sector))
    string i = str.lower(str.tostring(syminfo.industry))
    string t = "NSE:CNX500" // Default fallback
    string n = "Nifty 500"
    
    if str.contains(i, "bank") or str.contains(s, "finance")
        t := "NSE:BANKNIFTY"
        n := "Bank Nifty"
    else if str.contains(s, "technology") or str.contains(i, "software") or str.contains(i, "it")
        t := "NSE:CNXIT"
        n := "Nifty IT"
    else if str.contains(s, "health") or str.contains(i, "pharma")
        t := "NSE:CNXPHARMA"
        n := "Pharma"
    else if str.contains(i, "auto") or str.contains(s, "consumer durables")
        t := "NSE:CNXAUTO"
        n := "Nifty Auto"
    else if str.contains(s, "consumer non") or str.contains(i, "food") or str.contains(i, "beverage")
        t := "NSE:CNXFMCG"
        n := "FMCG"
    else if str.contains(s, "minerals") or str.contains(i, "steel") or str.contains(i, "metal")
        t := "NSE:CNXMETAL"
        n := "Metal"
    else if str.contains(s, "energy") or str.contains(i, "oil") or str.contains(i, "gas")
        t := "NSE:CNXENERGY"
        n := "Energy"
    else if str.contains(s, "real estate") or str.contains(i, "construction")
        t := "NSE:CNXREALTY"
        n := "Realty"
    else if str.contains(s, "infrastructure")
        t := "NSE:CNXINFRA"
        n := "Infra"
    [t, n]

